snippet.title: Why Rita Moreno thought the original "West Side Story" film wouldn't do well at the box office
snippet.description:
Rita Moreno recalls telling "West Side Story" co-star George Chakiris that she thought the 1961 film would struggle at the box office. It won 10 Oscars including best picture.

"60 Minutes" is the most successful television broadcast in history. Offering hard-hitting investigative reports, interviews, feature segments and profiles of people in the news, the broadcast began in 1968 and is still a hit, over 50 seasons later, regularly making Nielsen's Top 10.
